fullJobDescribtion:
What do we do?
We extract large amounts of data from different sources and transform it into business insights for various teams, such as: Finance, Performance Marketing, SEO, Affiliates, Influencers, Webutation, CRO, Product (apps, infrastructure, etc.).

What are we about?
Learning, developing, and finding the most efficient solution to a problem, is what we're all about. We create robust ETLs as well as elegant dashboards that enable other teams to monitor, plan, and fulfill their goals effectively.

Who works in our team?
Data analysts and engineers.

What tools do we use?
We use a bunch of tools like SQL, Looker, Google Cloud Services, Python, pandas, InfluxDB, Elasticsearch, Grafana.

If you want to:
Own and manage ETL processes;
Play a role in adopting Apache Airflow;
Empower teams to build actionable dashboards and informative deep dives;
Ensure the best data engineering practices;
Take direct actions to improve data quality through optimization, testing, monitoring, and tooling;
Be responsible for optimizing the overall technical data architecture;
Write clean code keeping in mind the differences between an ideal solution and a solution that works;
Follow CI/CD principles while writing code that is testable, efficient, and reusable;
Deliver data extraction and transformation solutions to the analyst team.

And this checks out:
Proven experience in data engineering or data development (2+ years);
Advanced knowledge in SQL, Git, CI/CD;
Previous practice in building ETL flows and data pipelines;
Willingness to mentor other colleagues;
The attitude and values of a true engineer.

Bonus points if you:
Have experience with Apache Airflow, Python, Google Cloud Platform: BigQuery, Data Fusion, Pub/Sub, dbt, InfluxDB, MongoDB, ElasticSearch.
Here’s the deal:
Gross salary 3100 - 6000 EUR/month (for Lithuanian market);
Choice of the tools you need to do your best;
Private health insurance and a physical health coach;
Half-day off on your birthday;
Flexibility regarding your work setting;
Additional vacation days depending on your tenure;
Half a day/month dedicated to learning with all the material you need;
Oh, and premium Surfshark accounts for you, your family and friends!

Job Title
Junior BI/Data Analyst (f/m/x)
As a part of Amadeus Hospitality & Media Distribution, travel audience unit is the world’s leading data-driven travel advertising platform. travel audience harnesses the power of home-grown tech, combined with cutting-edge machine learning practices to connect the leading performance-oriented travel brands with the biggest network of publishers, reaching Billions of travellers globally.

Our aim is to optimize advertising across the entire traveller journey, identify and create new audiences, and increase our partners' reach, relevance, and booking volumes.
We are looking for a Junior BI/Data Analyst to join our Data Analytics & Reporting team. You’ll be part of a team that is disrupting the industry with innovative attribution models and building the future analytics platform to be used by Amadeus customers worldwide for campaign performance and market insights. You’ll be working on very exciting projects using BigQuery, Composer, Tableau, PowerBI, all cloud-based solutions, and with terabytes of data coming from different sources.
What you'll do:
You'll learn several datasets at the company's disposal and how to use them in a meaningful manner;
You'll build and maintain visually appealing and engaging dashboards for external customers and internal stakeholders;
You'll support the team with data analysis requests from the different stakeholders;
You'll learn about our best practices and how to master Tableau, PowerBI, BigQuery and other tools and processes in use by the team;
You'll present data and insights in a clear manner with actionable outputs to the team and internal stakeholders.
Why us?
As part of our team, you will work in a highly motivated environment, with equal opportunities, flat hierarchies and short decision-making processes. You'll have a lot of freedom to contribute your own ideas and implement them. You will be a part of a diverse team with a strong sense of ownership that always goes beyond to make an impact while constantly learning and being truly passionate about Travel.
Drive innovation and develop tech solutions that bring value to our customers, and to make an impact on both the business and the market;
Join a fast-paced industry that is evolving every day while being backed by Amadeus, the biggest travel tech company in the world;
Be a part of an innovative environment where you are encouraged to research, explore, and try new ways of doing things;
Learn and develop – we offer a personalised approach to your development that combines a wide range of tools and programs, such as mentoring and coaching;
Enjoy your work-life balance – we provide Urban Sports Club membership, sabbatical options, certified experts in mental health and many more;
We got you covered - we offer visa and relocation support and assist you on other location-related topics along your journey with us;
Pick your hardware – we will set you up with the equipment you select for your daily working needs;
Smooth start - our extensive onboarding program and regular Team events facilitate your integration into our culture;
Make the most of our Travel perks - we offer travel insurance for you and your family, and a travel industry card with lots of benefits to explore;
Share company’s success – we offer a competitive bonus scheme and stock purchase options that every member can participate in.
About you:
Successfully completed a university degree in business informatics, information systems, economics, statistics, computer science, business administration or natural sciences;
SQL knowledge and are able to query and manipulate datasets - familiarity with Python or R is a plus;
Basic knowledge of BI platforms and how they can be used - some experience will be a plus;
Proven analytical and problem solving skills;
Passion for data exploration and visualisation;
Attention to details;
Good communication skills and are able to present information simply and directly;
Willingness to learn best practices of data analytics and visualisation;
You speak fluent English - our company's working language.
Diversity & Inclusion
We are an Equal Opportunity Employer and seek to hire the best candidate regardless of age, beliefs, disability, ethnicity, gender or sexual orientation.
